messages.message:
also, in these examples where it says “Cypress run failure”, even though the run actually passed, i see this error - could this be related to why `cypress_results.json` wasn’t created? @CJ
```You passed the --parallel flag, but we do not parallelize tests across different environments.

This machine is sending different environment parameters than the first machine that started this parallel run.

The existing run is: https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs

In order to run in parallel mode each machine must send identical environment parameters such as:

 - specs
 - osName
 - osVersion
 - browserName
 - browserVersion (major)

This machine sent the following parameters:

{
  "osName": "linux",
  "osVersion": "Ubuntu - ",
  "browserName": "Chrome",
  "browserVersion": "126.0.6478.182.... (Expected: 127)",
  "specs": [
    "apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/Settings/Account/edit-name.spec.ts",
    "apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/Settings/Oauth/oauth-crud.spec.ts",
    "apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/Settings/Organizations/members-crud.spec.ts",
    "apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/Landing/context-switching.spec.ts",
    "apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/Landing/login.spec.ts",
    "apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/Landing/send-product-feedback.spec.ts",
    "apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/Landing/view-apps.spec.ts",
    "apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/Landing/view-home-page.spec.ts",
    "apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/Billing/payment.spec.ts"
  ]
}

https://on.cypress.io/parallel-group-params-mismatch```
yes, this could definitely be related
the fix i made is a bandaid fix but this would be the root cause i think
we can pin the browser version in our config? but that'd mean we'd want to update it every time there's a new major
i wonder how the browser version is currently getting set?
i agree we could pin the browser version to solve the problem, updating it when there’s a new major version doesn’t sound too bad…
i think it's supposed to be the latest browser version? note that 127 released a week ago, so my guess is that the runners don't have a consistent chrome version
ok then let’s pin the browser version for now? and we’ll need to come up with some way for us to remember to update it when a new chrome version is released
